			<h4>Week 9</h4>
			<p><b>Baby : </b>Baby’s development in 9th week is very obvious . The spine gradually straightens out, between it and the head neck become obvious. Your baby ( the embryo )now shape like humans, just with head bigger compare to rest body. Eyelids cover the eyes for now. The mouth contains the beginnings of baby tounge, while future hair follicles show up on the head. Even The clear reflexes appear, for sucking and swallowing. </p>
			<p>The arms and legs keep becoming longer. The feet have lengthened noticeably, and the arms now have clear elbows. Dermal ridges, which form the baby's unique fingerprints, show up on the tiny fingers. The thumb separates out from the other fingers and migrates down the palm. The brain is rapidly developing; it's already separated into two hemispheres with rudimentary grooves. The pituitary gland, which required for growth and metabolism, and the cerebellum, which coordinates movement, can now been obvious. </p>
			<p>By the end of week 9 the baby’s thyroid is working, and the lymphatic system has begun to form and develop. The four-chamber heart pumps at 130–150 beats per minute, circulating blood through the entire tiny body. Mother and baby are connected via the umbilical cord, which contains three large blood vessels. The umbilical vein brings in oxygen-rich and nutritious blood, while the two umbilical arteries carry the embryo’s blood, full of CO2 (carbon dioxide) and waste products, out to the placenta.</p>

			<p><b>Mom : </b>This may difficult time – but as pregnancy advances week by week, you should start to feel better. </p>
			<p>You may have following sign and symptoms </p>
			<ul>
				<li>extreme tiredness</li>
				<li>nausea – find out about morning sickness remedies</li>
				<li>mood swings</li>
				<li>a metallic taste in your mouth</li>
				<li>sore breasts</li>
				<li>headaches</li>
				<li>new likes and dislikes for food and drink – anyone fancy mango chutney on their toast? Read our advice on weird pregnancy</li> <li>cravings</li>
				<li>a heightened sense of smell</li>
				<li>a milky white pregnancy discharge from your vagina</li>
				<li>light spotting (see your doctor if you get bleeding in pregnancy)</li>
				<li>cramping, a bit like period pains</li>
				<li>darkened skin on your face or brown patches - this is known as chloasma faciei or the “mask of pregnancy”</li>
				<li>thicker and shinier hair</li>
				<li>bloating and the feeling of being bloated</li>
			</ul>

			<p><b>Precautions & Tips</b></p>
			<p>At 9 weeks pregnancy you might struggle to button up your jeansdu to your belly. You can use loose fitting clothes or maternity pantsor  you can also use belly band or loop the elastic band in your jeans buttonhole.</p>
			<p>You and your fetus at 9 weeks need lots of nutrients and nourishment to have healthy growth. Increase the intake of folic acid, bit 12, calcium and iron during pregnancy by eating cheeses, broccoli, etc.To support your heavier and fuller breasts invest in a good maternity bra to relieve the soreness of your breasts.</p>
			<p>Be careful about Dehydration as it is not good for you vans  your 9 weeks baby development. Ensure that you drink lots of water and fluids. Eat fruits, vegetables and high fiber food to combat constipation and bloating</p>
			<p>You might not want to eat anything due to your morning sickness. However, don’t skip meals. Instead, divide your meals into several small meals and eat protein and carbohydrates rich food like toast biscuits.Take care of your posture, and avoid jerks to your body. Also, take adequate rest, avoid standing for long and keep yourself active through light exercises.</p>
			<p>Choose a safe exercise you can stick with for the rest of your pregnancy, like walking or yoga</p>
			<p>Be prepared for your breasts to feel fuller, heavier, and tender.</p>
		

