			<h4>Week 12</h4>
			<p><b>Baby : </b>In week 12, now the baby has plenty of  the amniotic fluid around him and it swallows a little fluid, which contains protein, fat, glucose, hormones, salts, and vitamins. The body processes the fluid swallowed, and the kidneys excrete it as urine and  the amniotic fluid is replaced every 3 hours. </p>
			<p>The baby can already make small movements, such as opening and closing its eyes, turning its head, pouting, and wiggling its fingers. On an ultrasound, you may see it open its mouth, clench and unclench its fists, suck its thumb, or cover its ears. You can hear the heartbeat, currently at 110–160 beats per minute, on a Doppler scan. </p>
			<p>The endocrine system begins to function, with the pituitary gland producing hormones responsible for growth and metabolism. Internal organs and systems continue to mature. The small intestine can now move food through in rhythmic motions, and the liver has started to produce bile. The cartilage making up the skeleton is gradually ossifying, using calcium from the mother’s body. So now mother required calcium more either from food they may inadequate so you have take medicine prescribed by your doctor.</p>

			<p><b>Mom : </b>By week 12, now you may start feeling much better.  Most of all pregnant women have reduced Morning sickness and  irritability gives way to a calm and harmonious state. </p>
			<p>The uterus may came  out of the pelvis and is rapidly expanding upward. Your lower abdomen protruding and  is now readily apparent. </p>
			<p>Now onwards you may start gaining weight. Due to nausea, vomiting, morning sickness struggling for food and it's smell you may loss weight. You may have increased appetite</p>
			<p>But don’t rush to eat for two. It’s better to take smaller meals throughout the day This helps avoid another common complaint in pregnancy, heartburn. Progesterone relaxes the valve separating the stomach and the esophagus, and stomach acid in the esophagus is what causes heartburn. A reasonable approach to eating, a nutritious and balanced diet, and regular, smaller meals throughout the day decrease its likelihood. </p>
			<p>you may begin experiencing cramps or pains in your legs. These symptoms suggesting a mineral deficiency, typically calcium or magnesium due to fetus is growing rapidly and takes the nutrients it needs to grow from the mother’s body. A balanced diet or vitamin supplements will help replenish your resources. </p>
			<p>You may have vaginal discharge clear or sticky White but it's normal is it doesn't associated with foul offensive smell, irritation, redness. </p>
			<p>If it is associated with blood or itching please contact your doctor.</p>

